Qinnovate Multi-License Structure
Copyright (c) 2026 Kevin Qi / Qinnovate

This repository contains multiple types of content under different licenses:

1. FRAMEWORK SPECIFICATIONS (CC BY-SA 4.0)
   QIF hourglass architecture, NSP protocol specification, TARA schema
   definitions, NISS scoring methodology, hourglass band definitions.
   License: https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/4.0/
   You may use, adapt, and implement freely with attribution.
   Modifications must be shared under the same terms.

2. THREAT REGISTRY DATA (CC BY-NC-SA 4.0)
   TARA technique entries, severity scores, therapeutic/diagnostic/governance
   projections, attack chain mappings.
   License: https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/4.0/
   Researchers may extend and publish for non-commercial purposes.
   Commercial use requires a separate license from Qinnovate.

3. BLOG POSTS & EDITORIAL CONTENT (CC BY 4.0)
   All blog posts, case studies, and editorial content.
   License: https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/
   Share, quote, excerpt, translate, republish freely — including
   commercially — with attribution to Qinnovate.

4. QIF WHITEPAPER (CC BY-ND 4.0)
   The QIF whitepaper and formal technical publications.
   License: https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nd/4.0/
   Share and cite freely — including commercially — with attribution.
   Must be shared in original, unmodified form.

5. WEBSITE CODE (MIT License)
   Astro components, layouts, styling, build configuration.
   See MIT license terms below.

For commercial licensing of the threat registry data or other permissions
not covered above, contact: kevin@qinnovate.com

Full licensing details: https://qinnovate.com/licensing/

